ISAAC MELNICK, APPELLANT, v. THE EAGLE GROCERY COMPANY, RESPONDENT. Submitted January term, 1935 Decided June 20, 1935.

Before Justices Lloyd, Case and Donges.

For the appellant, Sachs d Sachs. For the respondent, Martin J. Cummins. Pee Cubiam.

In this case no specification of determination in the trial court adequately presents any legal question for reversal. Booth v. Keegan, 108 N. J. L. 538; 159 Atl. Rep. 402; Grossman v. Lincoln Trust Co., 106 N. J. L. 567; 146 Atl. Rep. 376; Abbe v. Erie Railroad Co., 97 N. J. L. 212; 116 Atl. Rep. 778.

The judgment is affirmed, with costs.
